The paper deals with approximation algorithms for problems related to polygons and their intersection graphs, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of recursive partitioning schemes and balanced cuts suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). The problem of finding maximum weight independent sets is a classic problem in combinatorial optimization (cs.DM), and the paper also deals with sparsity conditions, which are often studied in theoretical computer science (cs.CC).
